                                   Introduction
                                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
          This manual assumes you are familiar with the RISC OS desktop. You
          may want to read the Welcome Guide and the User Guide#url
          http://acorn.riscos.com/riscos3/37/37DiscImage/Manuals/Manual/BOOKB/
          BOOK_3.HTM> that come with your RISC OS system.
          You may also want to read this introduction to RISC OS.
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
    !Meaning finds the meaning of acronyms and displays it in a textarea.
    You can select the text and drag the selection to other windows or copy
    it to the clipboard.
    New acronyms can be added.
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                                      Previous
                                                                          Next
    ==========================================================================

                                   Installation
                                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
      è   Download the program.
      è   The program is compressed into a Zip archive. Decompress it using
          e.g. SparkFS or Sparkplug#URL
          http://pilling.users.netlink.co.uk/free.html>.
      è   Copy the decompressed application, and any other files in the
          archive, to a place on your harddisc.
      è   That is it - you have installed Meaning.
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                                      Previous
                                                                          Next
    ==========================================================================

                                     Starting
                                     ~~~~~~~~
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
          Use the interactive help to get help on specific icons and
          menuitems.
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Running
        è    Double-click on the Meaning icon in the filer window to start
             the application. Meaning will put an icon on the iconbar.

                                                                        Page 1
        è    SELECT click on the iconbar icon to open the main window.
        è    Type an acronym into the writable icon and press enter. If
             Meaning knows the acronym it will display the meaning of the
             acronym in the textarea.

    Add new Acronyms
    The Data submenu of the iconbarmenu shows the files containing the
    acronym data, click SELECT on an entry to open the file. In these files
    every acronym has a seperat line and is followed by the meaning of the
    acronym also on a seperat line.

    When you have changed a data file and saved it you must SELECT the Renew
    entry in the iconbar icon to activate the changes. Clicking with ADJUST
    on the iconbaricon will also perform a renew.

    All data files are in the directory Choices:Meaning.Data. 
